<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="69" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/4928: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Des Fortes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                            Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-04T17:00:00-04:00">June 4, 1935—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>32. Foreign Minister informs me that Bolivia fully accepted this
                                afternoon third proposal of the mediators with modification that
                                there be definite commitment by both parties agreeing to arbitrate
                                should direct negotiations not succeed. He hopes for United States
                                support of such commitment.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>